  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Annual vine from Convolvulaceae, native to tropical Mexico. Herbaceous, twining vine producing ephemeral flowers that close by mid-morning. Flowers are funnel-shaped, typically purple-blue (purple-veined white, bicolored, or solid burgundy cultivars exist). Flowers mature acropetally along the inflorescence; each flower persists one morning. Pollinated by bumblebees and morning-flying bees. Seeds are hard-coated, toxin-containing (ergot alkaloid-like compounds), germinate slowly.",
